                                                                                                                         5                                                                                        SCIENCE amp;SPORTS                                                                
	THE STRANGEST MAN: THE HIDDEN LIFE OF PAUL DIRAC, QUANTUM GENIUS (Faber)
   By Graham Farmelo              
	Marvellous biography of a strange and silent scientist, who, with the equation named after him, revolutionized physics in the 20th century. The man and his science both come alive.                    
	HAROLD LARWOOD (Quercus)
   By Duncan Hamilton              
	Life of a truly great English fast bowler who went to live in Australia, where he had been forced to bowl bodyline by his captain, D.R. Jardine. Moving in the descriptions of his struggle and his lifelong obsession with Don Bradman.                    
	PERFECT RIGOR: A GENIUS AND THE MATHEMATICAL BREAKTHROUGH OF THE CENTURY (Houghton Mifflin Harcourt) 
  By Masha Gessen              
	Biography of one of the greatest living mathematicians, who solved Poincars Conjecture, one of the toughest mathematical problems. A complete recluse, he refused the Fields Medal, the equivalent of Nobel Prize for mathematics. Reveals how talented mathematicians were trained in the Soviet Union.                    
	OPEN: AN AUTOBIOGRAPHY (HarperCollins) 
  By Andre Agassi               
	Ironically, a most passionately anti-sports book by a superstar who claims that the game he mastered was a prison he spent some 30 years trying to escape.                    
	NO WAY DOWN: LIFE AND DEATH ON K2 (HarperCollins)
   By Graham Bowley              
	A chilling account of death on what mountaineers have come to call the killer mountain. On August 2, 2008, on a crowded mountain, 11 climbers died. Bowley recounts the encounter with death in a place where oxygen is a scarcity.                                                                                                                                                      
